14 PART I. DEFINITIONS.
15 1–701.
16 (a) [(1)] In this [section] SUBTITLE the following words have the meanings
17 indicated.
18 (B) “AT–RISK CENSUS TRACT” MEANS ANY GEOGRAPHIC AREA WITHIN A
19 1.5–MILE RADIUS OF THE BOUNDARIES OF:
20 (1) ANY CENSUS TRACT FOR WHICH THE FINAL EJ SCORE FROM THE
21 MARYLAND EJ TOOL IS AT OR ABOVE THE 75TH PERCENTILE IN THE STATE;
22 (2) ANY CENSUS TRACT FOR WHICH SIX OR MORE OF THE
23 ENVIRONMENTAL HEALTH INDICATORS IN THE DEFINITION OF “OVERBURDENED”
24 ARE AT OR ABOVE THE 75TH PERCENTILE IN THE STATE; OR
25 (3) ANY CENSUS TRACT FOR WHICH THE PROXIMITY TO:
26 (I) MINING OPERATIONS IS AT OR ABOVE THE 95TH
27 PERCENTILE IN THE STATE;
28 (II) EMITTING POWER PLANTS IS AT OR ABOVE THE 95TH
29 PERCENTILE IN THE STATE;
30 (III) A HAZARDOUS WASTE LANDFILL IS AT OR ABOVE THE 95TH
31 PERCENTILE IN THE STATE; OR

