23 [(5)] (I) “Environmental justice” means equal protection from
24 environmental and public health hazards for all people regardless of race, income, culture,
25 and social status.
26 [(6)] (J) “Environmental organization” means a nonprofit entity engaged
27 in advocacy, action, education, or job training related to conservation, stewardship of
