18 [(h)] (G) The Commission shall:
19 (1) Advise State government agencies on environmental justice and related
20 community issues;
21 (2) Use data sets and mapping tools to review and analyze the impact of
22 current State and local laws, permits, actions, and policies on the issue of environmental
23 justice and sustainable communities, including cumulative impacts, effects, and exposure;
24 (3) Assess the adequacy of State and local government laws to address the
25 issue of environmental justice and sustainable communities, including assessing
26 compliance with Title VI of the federal Civil Rights Act of 1964;
27 (4) Coordinate with the Children’s Environmental Health and Protection
28 Advisory Council, the Maryland Office of Minority Health and Health Disparities, and the
29 Commission on Climate Change on recommendations related to environmental justice and
30 sustainable communities;
31 (5) In accordance with [§ 1–702] § 1–705 of this subtitle, coordinate with
32 the Department on:

