20 (a) On or before December 31, 2023, the Department, in consultation with the
21 Commission on Environmental Justice and Sustainable Communities, shall:
22 (1) Subject to subsection (b) of this section, adopt a methodology for
23 identifying communities disproportionately affected by climate impacts;
24 (2) Develop specific strategies to address geographical impact concerns,
25 reduce emissions of greenhouse gases and co–pollutants, and build climate equity and
26 resilience within communities disproportionately affected by climate impacts;
27 (3) Set appropriate goals for the percentage of State funding for greenhouse
28 gas emission reduction measures that should be used for the benefit of disproportionately
29 affected communities; and
30 (4) Report to the Maryland Commission on Climate Change and, in
31 accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the General Assembly on the
32 policies and programs developed under this subsection.
33 (b) In evaluating methodologies under subsection (a)(1) of this section, the
34 Department shall, at a minimum, include:

