1 (1) Underserved communities;
2 (2) Overburdened communities; and
3 (3) Areas that are vulnerable to climate impacts, such as flooding, storm
4 surges, and urban heat island effects, due to low levels of tree coverage, high levels of
5 impervious surfaces, or other factors.
6 (c) In carrying out its responsibilities under this section, the Department shall:
7 (1) Solicit input from all segments of the population that will be impacted
8 by the policies developed under subsection (a) of this section, including individuals living
9 in areas that may be identified as disproportionately affected communities under the
10 proposed criteria;
11 (2) Ensure that equity and geographical impact remedies are key
12 principles; and
13 (3) Incorporate geographical impact considerations into all
14 recommendations, policies, programs, and funding priorities.
