17 PART III. ENVIRONMENTAL PERMITS.
18 1–708.
19 (A) (1) AN APPLICATION FOR THE ISSUANCE OR RENEWAL OF A COVERED
20 INDIVIDUAL PERMIT SHALL INCLUDE A BASELINE UNDERSTANDING OF RISK,
21 DISPARITIES, AND ENVIRONMENTAL NEEDS (BURDEN) REPORT PREPARED IN
22 ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SECTION.
23 (2) THE DEPARTMENT MAY NOT CONSIDER AN APPLICATION FOR THE
24 ISSUANCE OR RENEWAL OF A COVERED INDIVIDUAL PERMIT UNLESS THE
25 DEPARTMENT DETERMINES THAT THE APPLICATION INCLUDES A BURDEN
26 REPORT PREPARED IN ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SECTION.
27 (B) SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, A BURDEN REPORT
28 REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION SHALL:
29 (1) (I) DESCRIBE THE EXISTING ENVIRONMENTAL AND PUBLIC
30 HEALTH BURDEN FOR THE AT–RISK CENSUS TRACT IN WHICH THE SITE OR FACILITY
31 REQUIRING THE COVERED INDIVIDUAL PERMIT IS, OR WOULD BE, LOCATED; AND

12 HOUSE BILL 1268
1 (II) DESCRIBE THE POTENTIAL OR CURRENT CONTRIBUTIONS
2 TO THE EXISTING ENVIRONMENTAL AND PUBLIC HEALTH BURDEN BY THE SITE OR
3 FACILITY; AND
4 (2) AT A MINIMUM, INCLUDE:
5 (I) 1. THE EJ SCORE FROM THE MARYLAND EJ TOOL FOR
6 THE CENSUS TRACT IN WHICH THE SITE OR FACILITY IS LOCATED, INCLUDING A
7 DESCRIPTION OF THE INDICATORS CONTRIBUTING TO THE EJ SCORE; AND
8 2. THE EJ SCORES FROM THE MARYLAND EJ TOOL FOR
9 EACH CENSUS TRACT LOCATED WITHIN A 1.5–MILE RADIUS OF THE BOUNDARY OF
10 THE SITE OR FACILITY, INCLUDING A DESCRIPTION OF THE INDICATORS
11 CONTRIBUTING TO THE EJ SCORE;
12 (II) A COMPREHENSIVE LIST OF EACH EXISTING POLLUTION
13 SOURCE, OR CATEGORY OF SOURCES, THAT IS IMPACTING THE AT–RISK CENSUS
14 TRACT OR TRACTS WITHIN A 1.5–MILE RADIUS OF THE SITE OR FACILITY, INCLUDING
15 A DESCRIPTION OF POTENTIAL ROUTES OF HUMAN EXPOSURE TO POLLUTION FROM
16 EACH SOURCE OR CATEGORY IDENTIFIED;
17 (III) AMBIENT CONCENTRATIONS OF REGULATED AIR
18 POLLUTANTS AND REGULATED HAZARDOUS AIR POLLUTANTS;
19 (IV) 1. TO THE EXTENT INFORMATION IS AVAILABLE,
20 EXISTING TRAFFIC COUNT IN AT–RISK CENSUS TRACTS WITHIN 1.5 MILES OF THE
21 SITE OR FACILITY; AND
22 2. ANTICIPATED CONTRIBUTIONS TO THE TRAFFIC
23 COUNT FROM THE SITE OR FACILITY, INCLUDING VEHICLE TYPES, ASSOCIATED
24 EMISSIONS, AND ANTICIPATED ROUTES IN AT–RISK CENSUS TRACTS WITHIN 1.5
25 MILES OF THE SITE OR FACILITY;
26 (V) EXPOSURE OR POTENTIAL EXPOSURE TO CONTAMINATED
27 DRINKING WATER SUPPLIES IN AT–RISK CENSUS TRACTS WITHIN 1.5 MILES OF THE
28 SITE OR FACILITY;
29 (VI) PROXIMITY OF THE SITE OR FACILITY TO EXISTING
30 SOURCES OF POLLUTION;
31 (VII) THE POTENTIAL OR PROJECTED CONTRIBUTION OF THE
32 SITE OR FACILITY TO EXISTING POLLUTION BURDENS IN THE AT–RISK CENSUS

