27 ARE HIGHER THAN THOSE BORNE BY OTHER AREAS WITHIN THE STATE.
28 (3) IF THE DEPARTMENT DETERMINES THAT APPROVING AN
29 APPLICATION FOR A COVERED INDIVIDUAL PERMIT WILL CAUSE OR CONTRIBUTE TO
30 ADVERSE ENVIRONMENTAL OR PUBLIC HEALTH STRESSORS OR INDICATORS UNDER
